# NEXUS — professional test outline

When adding or editing tests under `NEXUS/` (any `*test*`, `*spec*`, or `NEXUS/tests/**`):

1. Follow **[NEXUS/docs/PROFESSIONAL-TEST-OUTLINE.md](NEXUS/docs/PROFESSIONAL-TEST-OUTLINE.md)** — file header block, suite metadata, arrange/act/assert, logging, cleanup, and `TEST_METADATA` / `testInfo` fields.
2. Respect NEXUS architecture: static scripts, `window.NX` / `NexusEngine`, WebGL; prefer **unit tests for pure logic**; use **browser runners** for GPU and recording paths; document **excluded** coverage (real GL, mic, MIDI hardware).
3. Cross-check user-visible flows against [NEXUS/QA-UPGRADE-MATRIX.md](NEXUS/QA-UPGRADE-MATRIX.md); reference matrix rows in suite `DESCRIPTION` when relevant.
4. No secrets in tests; validate URL/query inputs with allowlists; do not weaken mic/localStorage consent patterns for convenience.

If the user requests only a quick smoke test, still use the **header block** and **test id** convention (`NX-[AREA]-[NNN]`).
